Types of Problems in Text Data

Messy text data usually contains several issues such as slang words, abbreviations, emojis, spelling mistakes, repeated characters, and unnecessary punctuation.

These issues make it difficult for machines to understand the actual meaning of the text.

Preprocessing Techniques
Lowercasing – Convert all text into lowercase to maintain consistency.
Slang Normalization – Replace informal words like “u” with “you”.
Spell Correction – Correct incorrect words such as “gud” to “good”.
Emoji Removal or Conversion – Remove emojis or convert them into meaningful text.
Removing Punctuation – Clean unnecessary symbols like “!!!” or “??”.
Normalization of Repeated Characters – Convert “soooo” to “so”.
Tokenization – Split sentences into individual words.
Stopword Removal – Remove common words like “is”, “the”, “and”.
Stemming/Lemmatization – Convert words to their root form.